<p>&#8216;Putting tax payments or property transactions on blockchain &#8211; or issuing a Bank of England-backed digital currency &#8211; would help entrench English law as the forum of choice for resolving crypto disputes, the master of the rolls has said in a constitutionally daring intervention into policy-making.&#8217;</p>
